Over the years when I needed a moment to myself to gather my thoughts or just needed some time to meditate, I always find an open basketball court.

Focusing on making the same movement over and over in order to make a shot helps me get focused. Sometimes it works better than sitting in silence and meditating the traditional way.

Well I am not one for tradition. I focus on what works best for me and putting up hundreds is shots in hopes of hitting more than I miss has works wonders for me.

Keep shooting your shot!

What an amazing night‼️‼️

Huge shout out to @tacotuesdayopenmic for hosting the first ever Taco Tuesday’s Open Mic Awards at @ininebistro in the BRONX 

The birthplace of Hip Hop could not be more proud of these amazing artists. But not only hip hop artists were awarded on this night. Creators of a sorts were awarded for their efforts and achievements. 

I had the great honor of awarding “Best Rapper”to @raplikenico. It was even more special because he is also a Bronx native along with a couple other artists in the category. 

Full disclosure, I still suffer with dyslexia and there may not ever be a day that I don’t, but being brave enough to do something you are afraid of or have difficulty with is that part of life that helps mold you into the greatest version of yourself.

To anyone looking to display their talents, whether it’s music, dance, spoken word, comedy, you name it, check out @tacotuesdayopenmic. Just come and experience what the vibe is like and maybe it will inspire you to be the next winner of one of many categories that were presented last night. Also connect with like minded people on the same journey to greatness.

Great job by all the hosts, presenters, talent and a big shout out to all the people in attendance providing that positive energy all night‼️‼️

Proud of myself for having the courage to come back from one of my worst injuries in years, but please believe me when I say it’s been scary.

Now it’s time to put this body to the test.

I have always said “I hate running” but that’s not completely true. I like to run sprints. Give me a sprint over a long distance run any day.

Grateful to have @benswic to help me ensure that I am using proper form and technique‼️

I will show you my worst as I continue to improve these lost skills. 

If you want to come join us for Free. Check the link in @benswic bio to see the schedule.
